cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.MS, cs.SC 

The paper discusses parallelization and scalability analysis of inverse factorization of block-sparse Hermitian positive definite matrices, which is a problem in numerical linear algebra. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also uses the Chunks and Tasks programming model, which is a parallel programming model, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper deals with sparse matrices, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.MS (Mathematical Software). Finally, the paper discusses computational tests and performance analysis, which could also place it in cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Languages).
